 cadets work closely with faculty mentors in a unique one on one environment as they pursue scholarly research  A major goal of VCUR is to enhance the existing curriculum and elevate cadet standards and expectations  The Summer Undergraduate Research Institute  SURI  supports VCUR s goals by providing a structured program and financial support for research projects conducted during the summer at VMI  Cadets engage in in depth research with their faculty mentor while receiving course credit  It is a competitive application process  Please see the SURI website for complete details  VMI s Center for Undergraduate Research is an institutional member of the Council on Undergraduate Research  Learning Through Research  VMI s  Journal of Undergraduate Research  New Horizons   has been recognized by the Council on Undergraduate Research  CUR  as a model publication  The editors of VMI s New Horizons have been selected by CUR to collaborate with Oxford Brookes University to establish a framework in which peer institutions can develop similar publications that showcase student research  Applications and Deadlines There are funds available to assist in travel to conduct research or present the cadet s research findings  Submit an Undergraduate Research Cadet Travel Application along with a a statement of support from the mentor  Applications must be received at least two weeks prior to travel  If the request is for international travel  approval from the Office of International Programs is required before submitting the request for funding to V CUR  VMI also has funding dedicated to assisting in the purchase of research supplies  A Wetmore application must be submitted with a statement of support from the mentor  Cadets are responsible for submitting permits to the Commandant s Office for approval   Undergraduate Research  How to Begin Presenting Research Get Published   VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   